cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CE

The paper proposes a game-theoretic framework to model the cooperation behavior among multiple D2D operators and devices in a hierarchical LTE-A network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also deals with network communication and routing, which suggests the categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper proposes a cooperative model to improve the utility of operators and devices, which falls under the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper addresses decision-making problems among operators and devices, which is related to the category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
